From: Craig Miller <craig@nextidea.io>
Subject: [PATCH] wayle-styling: split comma-separated keyframe selectors

GTK4's CSS parser does not accept comma-separated keyframe selectors
(W3C-valid CSS animations syntax), emitting:

  Theme parser error: <data>:4461:5-6: Expected '{'
  Theme parser error: <data>:4461:5-6: Expected '}' after declarations

Split the two combined selectors in @keyframes blink into one rule each.

--- a/crates/wayle-styling/scss/modules/calendar_dropdown/_clock.scss
+++ b/crates/wayle-styling/scss/modules/calendar_dropdown/_clock.scss
@@ -24,12 +24,16 @@
 }

 @keyframes blink {
-    0%,
+    0% {
+        opacity: 1;
+    }
     50% {
         opacity: 1;
     }
-    51%,
-    100% {
+    51% {
+        opacity: 0.3;
+    }
+    100% {
         opacity: 0.3;
     }
 }
